Core Concept

TSC (λ) is a dimension-normalised coherence index:

λ(s) = ||s|| / (√d + ε)

Where:
	•	s = system state vector
	•	d = dimensionality
	•	ε = numerical stability constant

Interpretation

λ Range	Meaning
λ ≈ 0	Fully stabilised (projected)
λ < 0.01	Supra-coherent regime
λ → 1	Unconstrained divergence


